import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue', bins=30)
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of flight delays?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Delay (minutes)")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(data=data, y='distance')
    avg_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    plt.axhline(avg_distance, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    origin_counts = data['origin'].value_counts().reset_index()
    destination_counts = data['destination'].value_counts().reset_index()
    origin_counts.columns = ['location', 'count']
    destination_counts.columns = ['location', 'count']
    origin_counts['type'] = 'origin'
    destination_counts['type'] = 'destination'
    combined_counts = pd.concat([origin_counts, destination_counts])

    chart = sns.barplot(x='location', y='count', hue='type', data=combined_counts)
    plt.title('What is the most common origin and destination for flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Location')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.legend(title='Type')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='distance', y='delay', hue='origin', palette='tab10')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between delay time and distance?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Origin', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['date'] = data['date'].dt.date

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='date', kde=True, color='blue', bins=30)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight dates?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
